FBIS3-42184 "jptot005__l94038" JPRS-TOT-94-005-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 2 February 1994 WEST EUROPE TURKEY `Terrorists' Abduct Two Reporters in Southeast TA2901180694 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1457 GMT 29 Jan 94 TA2901180694 Ankara ANATOLIA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Istanbul, Jan 29 (AA) -- Terrorists from the outlawed separatist PKK [Workers Party of Kurdistan] organization abducted two reporters in Idil township in southeastern Sirnak Province on Friday. AA was told that the reporters were working for a private television channel (TGRT) and they were in the southeast to prepare a programme. No information was available from the reporters Kutlu Esendemir and Recep Ozturk. An investigation has been launched into the incident.
